# Frontend Patterns (React + Next.js)

Full monorepo and layer overview: @architecture.mdc.

## Tech Stack
- React 19 + Next.js 16 (App Router)
- TypeScript (strict)
- TanStack Query v5 + tRPC client (`@trpc/react-query` v11)
- REST client via Axios (`lib/api/client.ts`, `lib/api/v1` under `web/src`)
- Tailwind CSS
- Zustand (store middleware is mixed by store: some use `devtools + persist`, some only `devtools`, some plain `create`)
- next-intl (i18n runtime and translations)
- Telegram Mini App: `@telegram-apps/sdk-react`, `@telegram-apps/telegram-ui` (where WebApp behavior is needed)

## Web Structure (web/src)
- `app/` — App Router pages/layouts/routes
- `components/` — UI building blocks
- `features/` — feature-focused modules
- `hooks/` — reusable hooks (`hooks/api/*` for API-facing hooks)
- `stores/` — Zustand stores
- `contexts/` — React Context providers (auth/app mode)
- `providers/` — app-level providers (Query/tRPC)
- `shared/` — shared UI/helpers/state used across features
- `lib/` — client libraries and utilities
- `config/` — frontend runtime/static configuration
- `types/` — frontend types
- `i18n/` — i18n config/request setup
- `generated/` — generated artifacts (currently build info)
- `__tests__/` — tests
- Route handlers are also used in App Router (`app/**/route.ts`) for auth link flows.

## Meriter primary navigation

Canonical route helpers: `web/src/lib/constants/routes.ts`. There is **no** dedicated static URL such as `/meriter/birzha`; the МД («Биржа») hub is always `/meriter/communities/{communityId}` with `communityId` resolved at runtime.

### Bottom bar (`web/src/components/organisms/BottomNavigation.tsx`)

Shown on small viewports (`lg:hidden`). Tab order (left → right):

| # | Target | Path pattern | Label source |
|---|--------|--------------|--------------|
| 1 | Future Visions feed | `/meriter/future-visions` | `common.futureVisions` (e.g. RU «Образы будущего», EN «Future Visions») |
| 2 | МД hub (main weighted feed / «Биржа») | `/meriter/communities/{id}` — `id` from `useUserCommunities()` where `typeTag === 'marathon-of-good'`; if missing, tab falls back to `/meriter/profile` | `common.marathonOfGoodLabel` (e.g. RU «Биржа», EN default «Exchange») |
| 3 | Projects catalog | `/meriter/projects` | `common.projects` |
| 4 | Notifications | `/meriter/notifications` | `common.notifications` |
| 5 | Profile | `/meriter/profile` | `common.myProfile` |

Long-press on Profile opens a small menu (About, Support if `typeTag === 'support'`, Favorites, Log out).

### Left sidebar (`web/src/components/organisms/VerticalSidebar/VerticalSidebar.tsx`)

Desktop / large layout: same **three primary hubs** (Future Visions → МД → Projects), then Notifications, Favorites, etc. For the МД item, the link is `routes.community(marathon.id)`. When the sidebar is **expanded**, the МД row shows **`marathon.name`** from the API (community document), **not** `marathonOfGoodLabel` — so the visible title can match the long product name (e.g. «Биржа социальных инвестиций») if stored on the community. If **`marathon-of-good` is missing** from `allCommunities`, the sidebar **omits** the МД row entirely (the bottom bar still falls back the second tab to `/meriter/profile` when the id is missing).

### Global «Биржа» / МД feed: user-facing copy vs identifiers

Use this when wiring UI or docs so marketing names are not confused with `typeTag` / routes.

| User-facing (what players see) | Internal / technical (source of truth in code) |
|----------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------|
| RU short tab: «Биржа» (`common.marathonOfGoodLabel`) | Community `typeTag`: **`marathon-of-good`** |
| RU long form in help / projects copy: «Биржа Социальных Инвестиций» | Same community; display name may come from **`community.name`** (DB) or i18n strings — not a separate entity |
| EN tab default: «Exchange» | Bootstrap seed name for the hub is set in API (`PRIORITY_HUB_BOOTSTRAP` / `ensureBaseCommunities`); still keyed by **`marathon-of-good`** |
| «Лента» МД = weighted posts inside that community | **No** separate `feed` route key in the router; it is the **community page** for that id: `/meriter/communities/{marathon-of-good-id}` |

